GENITAL OPERCULUM (
Fig. 8C
). Wider than long, elliptical, separated with a pair of short male genital papillae.

PECTINES (
Fig. 8C
). Basal piece rectangular, notched on anterior median margin. Posterior margin of basal piece curved. Marginal lamella of 3/3 digits and median lamella of 7/7 digits, outer margin armed with a row of stout, short red setae and a few setae on surface. Fulcra 14/14, very small, roughly triangular, each armed with a few short red setae, placed in between adjacent pectinal teeth. Teeth 15/15, strong and stout.

TELSON (
Fig. 19B, E
). With stout vesicle, smooth on dorsal surface. Ventral median carina weakly granular, ending in triangular, subaculear, pointed nodule, armed with a pair of minute denticles on inner basal margin. Ventral portion with two weak carinae. Lateral and ventral intercarinal surfaces weakly granular. Aculeus strongly elongated.
